Have you ever purchased something off of Amazon that doesn’t have a single review? 😱😱 RISKY - right? 

As of now, cathclaire HAS! (Funny to think living on the edge for me used to look like getting a new tattoo and now it’s unreviewed amazon items)
I took a risk on this amazon set bc it LOOKED to have the adjustments to the usual amazon crinkle set that I have been pining for lately. 

Wide leg pants + a top with (dramatic) billowy sleeves with a tailored cuff. 

It is so comfy - yet casually over the top - which is always the goal.

Add your fave sneaks for the perfect airport outfit, an elegant heel for a more formal occasion, or something chunky if you want drama & height like me. 

BRB - going to write a review for this shop because showing love for things you enjoy is IMPORTANT!

Tips for wearing sweatpants:

Dress in terms of what you want to accentuate. For me, I want to elongate my legs and balance out the baggy pants with a form fitting or structured top to add a touch of a girly feel to my look. 

Pro tip: a third piece rounds out any outfit.

When I got dressed in these sweats, I wasn’t sure if I was going to BOTH the gym & to work away from home or just one of those errands. 

This outfit fit the bill and I felt *super confident*because Jessica Simpson has been wearing Free City since the early 2000s AND Whitney Port did her recent premiere on TikTok in them. 

You know where to go for links styled for you by me. Love you, fashionably and fully <3

Tips for styling A printed Piece for Work or Everyday Style: 

*offset w neutral colors - this will give your outfit a more laid back vibe

*build around it w your favorite basic (and reliable) pieces: here i paired this masai top w my wide leg pants from my amazon set 

*Mix dif textured fabrics to add dimension to your look 

I absolutely looooved working with @masai_us - a #sustainablefashion brand created BY women, FOR women. Not to mention this viscose top wears like a dream ✨ #masaicopenhagen #masaicopenhagenviscose

The second selfie is my favorite because it is my first ever selfie w baby Poppy, my college BFFS little girl 🥹🥹🥹🥹🥹 Cue all the feels.

Style the viral @skims dress with me 5 ways - a series 🎞 

This dress is one of my favorite pieces in my wardrobe - I love pieces that are versatile + flattering AF. It’s a full sentence on it’s own but SO fun to put your own twist on, style wise. 

First up - comfy, casual chic. Perfect for a travel day outfit
,  errands, or backyard hangs. 

I knotted an oversized t overtop of the skims dress, hiked it up a bit to show off the shoes, and topped it off w a pony tail + black flat brimmed hat. If you aren’t a hat person, skip that part! Make it your own, always. XO, Cath

#styleinspiration #skimsdress #getdressedwithme

Style the @Skims dress with me 5 ways - a series, pt. 2: Monochrome Pink

This monochrome pink look is not only flirty & feminine, but it is also demonstrating just how versatile this Skims dress is! 

Recreate this look by adding a variety of accessories or layers (I did a pink shirt, heels, and bag) to the SKIMS dress that are shades of one color. If you are in the mood for some dopamine dressing like I was- grab a bright, fun color or if you are in the mood to play it cool, stick to a neutral color like olive or taupe! 

Everything is linked on my LTK, as always. I also started an Amazon List with pieces inspired by this Skims styling series for all of my amazon bbs. 

XOX, Cath

#ltkfind #skimsdress #getdressedwithme

Decided to have a solo getaway to Keswick Hall with myself and it is one of the best decisions I have ever made. I timed it to be before my birthday so I could do some inner travel too <3 (A year in review is FUN!)

We are all familiar with the idea of taking yourself on a date,  but let’s take it a step further and say “take yourself on an overnight date at the most picturesque hotel where every single detail is exquisite and intentional” ie: @keswick_hall 

In terms of packing — I brought what I like to call: FULL GLAM. From my falsies to my special occasion Chanel eye patches, I treated myself like a celebrity. Highly recommend.

Favorite pieces I made sure to pack:
- Oversized Blazer
- Favorite high waisted denim
- Sparkly Heels
- A new pair of shoes 
- SKIMS body suit

If you are a millennial who remembers rushing home from school to catch your favorite music video on your television, I have a tried & true UNFORGETTABLE (birthday) party idea for you:

Outdoor Music Video Dance Party or in my case, *Cathella 

My inner child (and current self) is still jumping for joy after a night of dancing under the stars with my peeps, while watching larger than life music videos - esp Britney Spears. 

Shoutout to everyone who wished me a happy birthday and to my ladies that rolled up with not only their immaculate energy but ALSO: light up balloons, Moet, hair tinsel, flowers, cake, drinks galore, and gifts that made cathella more magical than I could have ever imagined. 

I beg of you to try this party idea, you won’t regret it <3 

PS - everything I ordered for this outdoor music video extravaganza is on my Amazon storefront! XO, Cath

#birthdaygirl #millennials #mtv #birthdayoutfit

Keswick Hall Stills —— 

I think we all know life isn’t always sunshine and roses, but let me tell you - it’s pretty close to sunshine and roses at @keswick_hall . 

I felt like a NEW woman when Kevin and Phoenix met me at Keswick after a retreat by myself. Can you tell? 

So here is your REMINDER to give yourself the gift of your own time and attention. If a getaway isn’t your thing rn, take yourself on a date or give yourself permission to take a break from your responsibilities to read a new book. You are worth it 💋

I am not exaggerating when I say some of my most vivid, memorable experiences have been during walking meditations with @drjoedispenza (or Daddy Joe as he is now known as on Tiktok w the cool kids 😂) ——-

💥 for the first time ever:

this unifying/transformative/FABULOUSLY-full-of -love-w-a-capital- L experience is open to the public, all over the world, at the same time, for 
no cost at all. 

Trust me when I say: this is a BIG DEAL. it costs the price of a designer bag for me to usually experience this AND these workshops where walking meditations take place usually end up w/ a waitlist!!!!! 

Regardless of your experience w meditation (honestly, novice meditators have an amazing track record) join the world (so far 90,000 people and 158 countries) at 10 AM EST this SATURDAY in Dr. Joe’s first ever Walk For the World 🌎 Imagine the impact your energy could have on the collective 🥹

I’ll be doing it with my family and friends in Virginia - and there are groups organized all over the world doing the same. Head to walkforthe.world for all the deets and to register to get the guided meditation! XO, Cath 💘💘

Back in RVA after the best weekend and our little family is still basking in the afterglow of a truly magical wedding ✨ 

Congratulations to our dearest friends @alexandraroussil & @proussil and thank you not only for an unforgettable wedding weekend, but for giving Phoenix an excuse to dress up like Boss Baby! WE LOVE YOUUUU! <3

STORY TIME: 

I didn’t allow myself to order a bridesmaid dress for @alexandraroussil ‘s wedding until exactly one month before the wedding. You can take one look at my style diary (ok, let’s call it what it is: IG feed and LTK profile) and quickly conclude that I hate wearing the color black. 

JK, it’s my favorite color to wear, my favorite dress to shop and I was very excited to find the perfect one for my best friends wedding. My point is, waiting until 30 days before the wedding was me flexing my muscle of self control because I knew I would order SO many black dresses and make up my mind way too many times, just to change it. 

This tulle masterpiece was a contender that arrived on our doorstep post our magical wedding weekend aka LATE. I literally laughed my butt off at the sight of the brown box on my doorstep because it is so indicative of the chaos that my life has been this past week. Sadly this is not an exaggeration in the usual cathclaire fashion, but *GLADLY* I am embracing all of the change and reminding myself that chaos always precedes order. 

* Editors note: Catherine is in love w the dress she got to wear on the big day ✨😆

Sometimes things have to break apart to come together in an even MORE beautiful way. Luckily, my little family has the best family and friends that anyone could ever ask for. Swipe to see the woman behind the lens AND the angel that got Phoenix ready in his ring bearer tuxedo (AND did his hair!) while mom and dad were doing their bridesmaid & groomsmen duties on 12.2.23 <3 

PS peep @rebeccapiersol rocking this dress to the wedding with a floral print overlay looking FLY af - pure elegance for bridesmaids, wedding guests, or holiday events!
